- app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostController.php

Explanation:
- The route /v1/posts/{post} in routes/api.php is mapped to App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostController@show. The implementation of this show method is located in the file app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostController.php.
- In that file, the show method is defined as public function show(Post $post): PostResource and returns a PostResource wrapping the given Post model.
- This confirms that the single file contains the handler implementation for the specified controller action. There are other PostController files (e.g., in Admin) and other methods in this same API controller, but the App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostController@show handler is implemented in the path listed above.
